        "title": "How to throttle a Flux",
        "body": "<p>Using Reactor, I would like to limit the rate at which events are published from a Flux, e.g. to a maximum of 10 Hz, while discarding all elements in between. The only thing I found is <code>delayElements()<\/code>, but this will queue up elements if they arrive at a faster rate, right? I'd like to some somethings like <code>someFlux.throttle(10).subscribe()<\/code> to make the Flux return at max. 10 elements a second.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 65773342,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "project-reactor"
        ],
        "score": 2,
        "accepted_answer_id": 65792305,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 2258
    },
    "question_comments": [],
